{"first_name":"Michael","last_name":"Schreck","permalink":"michael-schreck","crunchbase_url":"http://www.crunchbase.com/person/michael-schreck","homepage_url":"","birthplace":"","twitter_username":"mschreck1","blog_url":"","blog_feed_url":"","affiliation_name":"National Corrective Group","born_year":null,"born_month":null,"born_day":null,"tag_list":"","alias_list":null,"created_at":"Tue Nov 23 18:42:21 UTC 2010","updated_at":"Sat Oct 13 04:04:59 UTC 2012","overview":"<p>Chief Executive Officer &amp; Senior Operating Partner Specializing In Private Equity-Backed Growth Companies.</p>\n\n<p>SaaS Growth/CEO Leadership:</p>\n\n<p>Directed the global expansion of Zmags digital publishing business into the rapidly developing mobile and social commerce markets. Clients include over 40% of the apparel firms listed on the Fortune 500 and 60% of the business services firms listed on the Global 100.</p>\n\n<p>Emerging Growth/Private Equity Leadership:</p>\n\n<p>Presided over three start-ups that recruiting exceptional talent and top P/E co-investors. The results: M-Qube pioneered the mobile marketing space (acquired by VeriSign for $250 million), Upromise is the leading 529 investment platform (acquired by SLM for $300 million) and SmartBargains/Rue La La was acquired by GSI Commerce for $350 million. Adviser, investor and board member to a number of emerging-growth companies.</p>\n\n<p>Interim CEO/Advisory Leadership:</p>\n\n<p>Significant interim executive/advisory deployments for top-tier private equity firms. Examples: Directed turnaround at Metabolife that restored $300 million nutraceutical leader to profitability, interim senior leadership for CEO and CMO of a multi-billion dollar entertainment company.</p>\n\n<p>Business Services/CEO Leadership:</p>\n\n<p>Doubled EBITDA at National Corrective Group as CEO/President. Leading national business/government-services platform. Completed a mid $8-figure sale to a leading private equity firm. </p>\n\n<p>Strategic/ diligence re